name: Bugolution #2
description:
Daniel Mank
Digital Illustration
2021

The "Bugolution" series is comprised of 21 digital works. It was created by the artist influenced by the aesthetics of entomology and botany.
Each of the illustrations showcases the complex biological processes and interactions that take place in the kingdom of plants, mushrooms and insects. The main image that the author uses is the root system. It symbolizes the brain, the center of control and transmission of information in the forest ecosystem.
